parameters:
Chancellor: What's this? I hear reports of an intruder
wreaking havoc, and who do I find but you? You're quite
late, Knight.
Chancellor... it was all your scheme...!

Chancellor: How did your search for the holy sword go?
Kukuku... Did you find the non-existent blade?

Chancellor: Hmph, this is the problem with knights... always
so hot-blooded.

I'm relieved to see that even after a long tenure as
Chancellor, your body hasn't grown dull. Now I can cut you
down without holding back.

Chancellor: Isn't it your body that has grown dull? What's
wrong, your movements lack sharpness?

Chancellor: Did 'something' happen on your way here? For
example, something like your womanly dignity being trampled
upon.
00_st_pri_a01
Princess: Ahh... ugh... ah...!!
Princess: Is there... someone there? Ahh... ahh...!!
Ah, Princess-sama!?
What in the world...

You bastard, Chancellor!! To lay hands on your own
sovereign!!

Chancellor: Hmph. I never once thought of this girl as my
lord.

Chancellor: The only one I ever swore loyalty to was the
previous king alone.
You are such a person...!

Chancellor: By the way, Reisha, did you read the documents
in my study?
The memoirs in the study?

If you wish to skip content due to repetition, I recommend
selecting "I read it." If you are interested in the story,
select "I haven't read it."
I've read it.
I haven't read it.
読んだ。

Chancellor: I see, that makes things quicker and easier for
me.
説明スキップ
読んでいない。

Chancellor: Why I would lay hands on the princess? If you
want to know, I shall tell you. Now, where should I begin...

Chancellor: Tell me, Reisha, do you know? There's a secret
in the royal bloodline.
A secret, you say...?

Chancellor: Why are there so many short-lived individuals in
the royal lineage? Why are there inherent differences in the
order of succession from birth?

Chancellor: The fact that many past kings began to show
their talents, and the more brilliant they shone, the more
madly they raged, leading to tragic ends.

Chancellor: The words of regret that slipped from the lips
of His Highness the Crown Prince amidst the recent
succession turmoil, 'My royal blood is thin.'

Chancellor: The illness of His Highness the Crown Prince,
the defection of His Highness the elder brother, the
uncharacteristic frenzy and death of the wise previous king.

Chancellor: The words of His Highness the elder brother made
many things click into place. And from that day I heard
them, I became obsessed with the royal blood.

Chancellor: The existence of a special magical power
mediated by blood. A secret magic that slumbers only within
certain lineages and is passed down through generations.

Chancellor: Using my position and gaining collaborators, my
research advanced. The relationship between the blood
flowing within humans and magic reached profound depths.
Chancellor: But what of it?

Chancellor: The only girl who possesses the royal bloodline
I most wanted to understand was closest to me, yet her
temperament was farthest from what I desired. Isn't it
laughable?

Chancellor: She doesn't sway with profit nor tolerate
deceit. She's steadfast in her love for her country. She
must know full well that without my connections and skills,
governance would falter.
Chancellor: It was quite a struggle to get close to her.

Chancellor: She was a sullen princess difficult to handle,
but why is it, Reisha? When your name comes up, she
immediately takes interest. You are greatly trusted by her.

Chancellor: She listened intently with shining eyes when I
spoke of our time at court school where I briefly instructed
you. Such an adorable thing. Unaware of what would befall
her later.

Chancellor: To capture her... perhaps that sounds too harsh.
I invited her here to cooperate with our magical experiments
and then I understood.

Chancellor: The legendary sword "Sword of Dawn" from the
royal family's lore. Its brilliance is said to lead the
country to dawn as a supreme treasure, that's its true
nature.

Chancellor: It is said that kings with particularly strong
royal bloodlines and awakened magical powers could extract
immense magical energy from their own blood and materialize
it.

Chancellor: The blood-soaked sword overwhelms everything,
and with unparalleled power, it thunders the path of
conquest upon this land. Its form, turning soldiers to dust
and battlefields to scorched earth, is a weapon itself. To
think such a thing is considered a supreme treasure.

Chancellor: It's laughable, isn't it? The royal family's
supreme treasure, thought to be lost, is in my hands, and
yet, despite that, everyone has forgotten it, and the
country is declining like this.

Chancellor: Have you ever experienced it? The feeling of
being able to do nothing but watch as the country you
believed in weakens.

Chancellor: That's why I will revive it. I will awaken the
royal blood and with magic, make this country resound
throughout the world!!

Chancellor: I will take the first step on the path of
conquest that the king I swore loyalty to could not
achieve!!
説明スキップ
Chancellor: Your existence was an obstacle to my plans.

Chancellor: You live by the knight's code of this country,
not swayed by profit and sticking to righteousness. I knew
you would never lend an ear to my true intentions.

Chancellor: It would be troublesome if it caused a stir. I
wanted to take care of this nuisance before my plans were
discovered, and then I received some useful information.

Chancellor: It would be good if I could send your existence
far away, and even better if you perished on your journey. A
knight abandoning their mission and returning empty-handed
is something you would never allow yourself.

Chancellor: "You" will obey if it's "for the lord," and "our
king" will easily accept my opinion if it's said "for the
knight."

Chancellor: Bonds and emotions can sometimes cloud one's
eyes, you half-baked lot.

Is that all you have to say? Are you planning to give a
speech at this late hour?

I understand what you want to say. If you're expecting me to
panic and reconsider at this point, then you're sadly
mistaken.

If buying time is your aim, it's transparent. Don't bother
asking me to change my mind now. The sights I've witnessed
are more than enough reason to cut you down.
Take care not to let this sword strike fly immediately...!!

Chancellor: Hmph, so it is. This is why knights are
problematic. Always quick to fight, first and foremost.

Chancellor: Although, as it stands now, I am in the position
of a knight protecting the monarch. The first step of my
conquest. I've finally obtained it; there's no way I'm
giving it back!

I will never allow you to speak of chivalry with that
mouth!!

Chancellor: Unable to sense danger, leaving the lord you
should protect exposed to peril, and on top of that, running
around on a journey orchestrated to search for a non-
existent holy sword.

Chancellor: What else can this be called but foolishness? If
such is what you call knighthood, then I have no need for
it.
Gah...!

Chancellor: It's been a long time since I've been away, but
don't forget that I too once took up the sword and fought
for the country.
Chancellor: Although strictly speaking...

Chancellor: My talents were better suited for this side of
things.

To our lord... no, not just that. For the many sins you've
committed against those you've laid hands on, your body has
more than enough to atone for.

All your past atrocities, don't ever think they will be
forgiven...!!
Chancellor: Don't underestimate me, you outdated knight!

Chancellor: The time for the awakening of the royal
bloodline is near! If you intend to interfere with my plans,
I will show no mercy──!
Chancellor: Here I go...──!!
